Frances L. Allen: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 25, 2017 11:26 PM ET
Hotels, Restaurants and Leisure

Company Overview of Jack in the Box Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Frances L. Allen  President of Jack in the Box Brand, Jack in the Box Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 5 different industries.55$1,984,057As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Ms. Frances L. Allen has been the President of Jack In The Box Brand at Jack in the Box Inc. since October 27, 2014. Ms. Allen served as a Brand Marketing Officer of Dunkin' Donuts Incorporated since June 4, 2007. She served as the Chief Brand Officer of Denny's Corporation from June 2013 to September 19, 2014. She served as an Executive Vice President of Global Strategy of Denny's Corporation since June 2011. She served as an Executive Vice President of Denny's Corporation ... from July 2010 to September 19, 2014. She served as the Chief Marketing Officer of Denny's Corporation from July 2010 to June 2013. Ms. Allen served as Chief Marketing Officer of Dunkin' Brands from 2007 to 2009. She served as a Senior Vice President with DMB&B based in Hong Kong. She joined Dunkin' Donuts from Sony Ericsson Mobile Communications where she served as its Vice President of Marketing from 2004 to 2007. She served as Chief Marketing Officer for Dunkin Donuts, where she was instrumental in increasing sales by launching healthier menu options and several successful marketing campaigns. Prior to that, she worked at PepsiCo in a number of leadership roles. She served as Vice President of Innovation for Pepsi-Cola North America and oversaw the creation of new products, new packaging, equipment and merchandising and also helped direct its strategy and programs for health and wellness. While at Frito-Lay, a division of PepsiCo, she served as Director of international advertising, handling the launch of the Lays, Doritos and Cheetos brands into new global markets. Ms. Allen served as Chief Marketing Officer of Dunkin' Brands from 2007 to 2009. From 1998 to 2004, she held several positions at PepsiCo, as Vice President of Marketing. She held several positions with that agency, served as Senior Vice President, Worldwide Account Director. She has more than 30 years of branding and marketing experience, including senior leadership roles at such major organizations as Denny's, Dunkin' Brands, Sony Ericsson Mobile Communications, PepsiCo and Frito-Lay. She served as a Director of Marinemax Inc. from November 18, 2013 to April 2015. She served as a Director of The Advertising Council, Inc. since May 2009. She began her career in 1983 at a London-based advertising agency, Benton & Bowles, which subsequently became D'Arcy Masius Benton & Bowles (DMB&B). She was named "Marketer of the Year" in 2009 by BrandWeek Magazine. Ms. Allen holds a BS in mathematics from the University of Southampton, England and completed the Advanced Management Program at Harvard Business School.Read Full Background




